.TH "zynq_gpio_set_value" 9 "zynq_gpio_set_value" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zynq_gpio_set_value \- Modify the state of the pin with specified value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" zynq_gpio_set_value
.BI "(struct gpio_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pin "  ","
.BI "int state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
gpio_chip instance to be worked on
.IP "pin" 12
gpio pin number within the device
.IP "state" 12
value used to modify the state of the specified pin
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function calculates the register offset (i.e to lower 16 bits or
upper 16 bits) based on the given pin number and sets the state of a
gpio pin to the specified value. The state is either 0 or non-zero.
